redible cosmic phenomena. Joshua Bloom gives readers a concise and accessible overview of gamma-ray bursts and the theoretical framework that physicists have developed to make sense of complex observations across the electromagnetic spectrum. He traces the history of remarkable discoveries that led to our current understanding of gamma-ray bursts, and reveals the decisive role these phenomena could play in the grand pursuits of twenty-first century astrophysics, from studying gravity waves and unveiling the growth of stars and galaxies after the big bang to surmising the ultimate fate of the universe itself. What Are Gamma-Ray Bursts? is an essential primer to this exciting frontier of scientific inquiry, and a must-read for anyone seeking to keep pace with cutting-edge developments in physics today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGamma ray bursts. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Astrophysics.2bisacsh  aGRB afterglows.  aGRB.  aGRBs.  aNASA GRB satellite.  aPartial Test Ban Treaty.  aRay Klebesadel.  aSwift satellite.  aVela Satellite Program.  aX-ray emission.  aafterglow emission.  aafterglow theory.  aafterglow.  aafterglows.  aanomalous X-ray pulsars.  aastronomers.  aastrophysics.  abig bang.  acentral engine behavior.  acosmic phenomena.  acosmic rays.  adust.  aelectromagnetic spectrum.  aexplosion propertie.  agalaxies.  agamma-ray bursts.  agas.  agravitational waves.  agravity waves.  ahigh-energy emission.  aneutrinos.  aneutron stars.  anuclear testing.  apanchromatic observations.  aprogenitors.  areionization.  arelativistic shocks.  ascientific inquiry.  asoft Gamma-ray Repeaters.  astar formation.  asupernova.  ayoung stars.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-20